.TH "voltdm_scale" 9 "voltdm_scale" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
voltdm_scale \- API to scale voltage of a particular voltage domain.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" voltdm_scale
.BI "(struct voltagedomain *voltdm "  ","
.BI "unsigned long target_volt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "voltdm" 12
pointer to the voltage domain which is to be scaled.
.IP "target_volt" 12
The target voltage of the voltage domain
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This API should be called by the kernel to do the voltage scaling
for a particular voltage domain during DVFS.
